I agree with you (I sent the original email suggesting this back in 2006). This is noted in the spec source as a &quot;v2&quot; feature that might be added to the spec in the future: <blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />&lt;!-- Proposals for v2:<br />       * &lt;select value=&quot;&quot;&gt; as an alternative to &lt;option selected&gt;<br />         <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://developers.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=426306&amp;cid=22142072">http://developers.slashdot.org/comments ... d=22142072</a><!-- m --><br />         &lt;Philip`&gt; <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.ipiao.com.cn/">http://www.ipiao.com.cn/</a><!-- m --> does &lt;select size=&quot;1&quot; name=&quot;to&quot;&gt;&lt;script&gt;City_Default=&quot;PEK&quot;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;SCRIPT language=javascript<br />                   src=&quot;/js/flightcity.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/SCRIPT&gt;&lt;/select&gt; which is the kind of thing that could be much simpler with &lt;select value=&quot;PEK&quot;&gt;<br />       * a way to make the &lt;select&gt; not have a default value at all (ack<br />         or to have a &quot;placeholer&quot; like value that doesn't count as a value being selected but shows a prompt until a value is selected<br />       * once we can have no default, a way to require=&quot;&quot; a value.<br />       ack Weston Ruter: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://weston.ruter.net/projects/test-cases/html-select-element/">http://weston.ruter.net/projects/test-c ... t-element/</a><!-- m --><br />       q.v. <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://lists.whatwg.org/pipermail/whatwg-whatwg.org/2008-November/017583.html">http://lists.whatwg.org/pipermail/whatw ... 17583.html</a><!-- m --><br />    --&gt;<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />It's relatively easy to work around the lack of this feature with some script, though.<br /><br />If you want this soonish, I'd suggest you send an email to whatwg or file a bug in W3C bugzilla summarizing use cases for this feature, and maybe try to convince browser vendors to add this feature (e.g. by filing bugs).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Tue Nov 10, 2009 11:32 pm</p><hr />
