<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=180&amp;p=702#p702"><![CDATA[
Is it just wrong implementation in Opera and Weston Ruters' JavaScript that empty select value ignores by validator? If so, I think that it should be clarified in specs.<br /><br />See <a href="http://rusrestaurant.com/tests/webforms2/validation/select-required.html" class="postlink">test page and further explanation here</a>.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Update:</span> I see now that there is no required attribute for select in specs.<br />Probably this should be corrected to allow required attribute for SELECT. In <span style="font-style: italic">most</span> cases SELECTs have first option blank or &quot;please select&quot; with no or empty value, so SELECT needs validation.<br /><br />Also consider to make invalid (if field is required) check boxes and radio buttons with empty value. It may be helpfull in some cases.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=129">FataL</a> — Thu May 01, 2008 9:36 pm</p><hr />
